        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 5:19PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Dahlonega, moving north
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Camp Merrill, Whitley Gap Shelter, Blue Mountain Shelter, Woods Hole
Shelter, Low Gap Shelter, Blairsville, Camp Coleman Lake, Owltown,
Suches, Vogel State Park, Track Rock, Porter Springs, Turners Corner,
Blood Mountain Shelter, Dahlonega, Gaddistown, Gooch Mountain
Shelter, and Garland.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
